In a press briefing, White House spokesperson Karine Jean-Pierre discussed several foreign policy announcements, including President Biden's call with Ukrainian President Zelensky and the US's commitment to providing additional security assistance and humanitarian aid to Ukraine. She also mentioned the President's upcoming trip to Saudi Arabia and his intention to meet with Saudi leaders, including Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman. Jean-Pierre highlighted the President's efforts to lower gas prices and called on oil companies to increase refining capacity and lower costs for consumers. She mentioned the President's plan to sign an executive order advancing equality for LGBTQI+ individuals and his support for DACA recipients on the 10-year anniversary of the program. Finally, Jean-Pierre mentioned the administration's focus on monitoring extreme heat conditions and addressing the impact of climate change.